gujarati.context:
Here is the translation:

The moon of Karka appears in the sky, its name is Hari so it is said; 
One who has none, will lose everything, all calamities will be ended by Hari.

Here is the translation:

God is like Haridas and Hanuman, ever devoted to Him; 
Krishna's eternal love is being told, Pralhad will be born of it.

Here is the translation:

God stays in His commandment, and He gives you, like an untouched pearl; 
The Lord takes away your material identity, and you become a devoted and unblemished one.

Hands hold the signs of Padmanabhan, it is seen; 
Face beholds a thousand waves, it is hidden. 

The upper curve is the eight-cornered flag, it is raised; 
The swastika is the anchor of Ambuj, it is tied up.

Here is the translation:

Death saw a jambu fruit, a vajra to see, at that time it shone on the south foot; 
Fish saw a triangle of fortune, and cattle saw a fortunate day.

Here is the translation:

He makes character by his actions, not by words alone; 
Mother and father are brother and sister to him, whoever is with whom he lives.

Here is the translation:

Keep with God's help and company, many are waiting too; 
Loving human and woman is necessary but not getting with one's parents' hands.

Here is the translation:

Foolish love does not give, nor take, ever; it is done out of desire, never; 
without anxiety, calmness, and beauty, one's own reasons do not wish that, that very thing.
